author: Adam Savage’s Tested
description:
Before wrapping up our most recent visit to Propstore, Adam and Norm continue their tradition of examining Star Trek filming models. This time, we check out the massive close-up model of the USS Enterprise with incredibly detailed hull damage it sustained in Star Trek II: The Wrath of Kahn. Adam explains how this kind of battle damage would be created in the ILM model shop, and we admire the intricate details of this beautiful miniature!

Learn more about the upcoming Propstore EMLA: Los Angeles summer 2025 auction at https://propstoreauction.com/auctions/info/id/456

Shot by Joey Fameli and edited by Norman Chan
Music by Jinglepunks
